    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1891-09-16T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1891-09-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="179"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d179">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Egan</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Blaine</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1891-09-16">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 16, 1891</hi>.</date> (Received November
                        13.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 202.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to state that a decree has been
                    issued by the Provisional Government ordering an election of members of the
                    Senate and House of Deputies and of Presidential electors, to take place on the
                    18th October next, and it has fixed the 26th of December next as the date of
                    inauguration of the President who shall be elected.</p>
                <p>Up to the present there is absolutely no certainty as to who will be chosen for
                    the Presidency, but from the most reliable information I can gather I am led to
                    believe that the Conservative or Clerical party, although now feeling quite
                    confident of a majority in the Chamber of Deputies, will not be able to elect
                    more than about thirty out of ninety-four members, and that in the Senate of
                    forty-one members they will not have over six adherents.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Patrick Egan</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
